<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="82" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[131,777,215,1428]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">
DISTRIBUTION. — 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[311,441,773,797]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">
<collectingCountry box="[311,441,773,797]" name="United States of America" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">United States</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. This species “seems to be confined to the eastern states. Bailey gives the range as from New England to 
<collectingRegion box="[160,243,824,848]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Virginia</collectingRegion>
. It is a common, but not a very productive blackberry in old fields and fencerows in the hills of 
<collectingRegion box="[549,675,850,874]" country="United States of America" name="Pennsylvania" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Pennsylvania</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="West Virginia" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">West Virginia</collectingRegion>
.’’ (as stated in 
<bibRefCitation author="DAVIS H. A. &amp; FULLER A. M. &amp; DAVIS T." box="[357,589,877,901]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="235 - 266" refId="ref17164" refString="DAVIS H. A., FULLER A. M. &amp; DAVIS T. 1969 b. - Contributions toward the Revision of the Eubati of Eastern North America. V. Arguti. Castanea 34 (3): 235 - 266. https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 4032358" type="journal article" year="1969">
Davis 
<emphasis box="[419,466,877,901]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
1969b: 261
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[131,777,215,1428]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,287,908,932]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Southern AFrica</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Beek &amp; Widrlechner, 2021" authorityName="A. Beek &amp; M. P. Widrlechner" authorityYear="2021" box="[298,427,906,930]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revealii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[298,427,906,930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Rubus revealii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[431,504,907,930]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is an invasive species in parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[157,283,933,957]" name="South Africa" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, especially in the north of 
<collectingRegion box="[542,689,933,957]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Kwazulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
, the east of the 
<collectingRegion box="[200,300,959,983]" country="South Africa" name="Free State" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Free State</collectingRegion>
, and the southeast of Mpumelanga, and also in 
<collectingCountry box="[134,234,985,1009]" name="Swaziland" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Swaziland</collectingCountry>
. In Kwazulu-Natal, it is accompanied by two other invaders from North America, 
<taxonomicName authority="L. H. Bailey" authorityName="L. H. Bailey" box="[378,614,1012,1036]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="probabilis">
<emphasis box="[378,496,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">R. probabilis</emphasis>
L.H. Bailey
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="L. H. Bailey. In" authorityName="L. H. Bailey. In" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="originalis">
<emphasis box="[662,774,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">R. originalis</emphasis>
L.H. Bailey. In
</taxonomicName>
South African publications (
<bibRefCitation author="STIRTON C. H." box="[556,680,1038,1062]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="101 - 106" refId="ref19029" refString="STIRTON C. H. 1984. - Notes on the genus Rubus in southern Africa. Bothalia 15: 101 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.4102 / abc. v 15 i 1 / 2.1108" type="journal article" year="1984">Stirton 1984</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HENDERSON L." pageId="17" pageNumber="82" refId="ref17766" refString="HENDERSON L. 2001. - Alien Weeds and Invasive Plants: a Complete Guide to Declared Weeds and Invaders in South Africa, Including Another 36 Species Invasive in that Region. Agricultural Research Council, Pretoria, 300 p. (Plant Protection Research Institute Handbook 12)." type="book" year="2001">Henderson 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="HENDERSON L." box="[237,287,1065,1089]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref17817" refString="HENDERSON L. 2011. - Rubus species - brambles, blackberries and others. SAPIA News 19: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
), these three taxa have usually been considered as forms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pursh. More" authorityName="Pursh. More" box="[214,461,1091,1115]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuneifolius">
<emphasis box="[214,336,1091,1115]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">R. cuneifolius</emphasis>
Pursh. More
</taxonomicName>
recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="SOCHOR M." box="[548,687,1091,1115]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" refId="ref18896" refString="SOCHOR M. 2018. - Preliminary taxonomic treatment of eastern South African Rubus. Crop Research Institute, Olomouc, 44 p." type="book" year="2018">Sochor (2018)</bibRefCitation>
correctly conceived the samples of 
<taxonomicName authority="Beek &amp; Widrlechner, 2021" authorityName="A. Beek &amp; M. P. Widrlechner" authorityYear="2021" box="[378,472,1118,1142]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="revealii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[378,472,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">R. revealii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[478,553,1118,1141]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[601,713,1118,1142]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rubus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="originalis">
<emphasis box="[601,713,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">R. originalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as belonging to the 
<emphasis box="[274,333,1145,1168]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">Arguti</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="82" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="17.[131,777,215,1428]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82">
PICTURES. — 
<bibRefCitation author="HENDERSON L." box="[276,466,1194,1219]" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 9" refId="ref17817" refString="HENDERSON L. 2011. - Rubus species - brambles, blackberries and others. SAPIA News 19: 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="2011">Henderson (2011)</bibRefCitation>
: 1a and c; 2: the upper series; 3: the upper series.
</paragraph>
